RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y All Weather Track CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 21000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONFER was unhurried in the three to four paths, tipped inwards to the two path and was roused into the far turn, advanced between foes and floated out to the six path while taking aim at the top of the lane, stayed on to bid while drifting in passing the eighth pole, and inched past an inner rival in the closing stages to win. FAR ABOVE stalked in the four path, bid under a nudge from the three path early around the far turn, took a narrow lead and was urged from the five path into the stretch, ran on while drifting in into the final furlong, but was caught by an outer foe late to place. LA DAME DE FER bumped with an outer foe at the start, tracked inside, swung out to the four path into the stretch, and kept on for show. BULLET VALENTINA bumped with an inner foe at the start, set the pace in the two path, shifted inside and was put to a ride when challenged early around the far turn, was cued left handed from the two path at the top of the lane, but yielded passing the eighth pole. QUEEN ROCKET rated in the five path but was empty entering the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: La Dame de Fer
ENTRY.COMMENT: bump start,track inside,swung4p into stretch,kept on for show

ENTRY.NAME: Bullet Valentina
ENTRY.COMMENT: bump start,pace2p,shifted inside into far,2p top lane,yielded1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Far Above
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalk4p,bid3p far turn,lead,urge5p upper,ran on drift in,caught

ENTRY.NAME: Confer
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried3-4p,2p far turn,aim6p upper,drift in,bid1/8,inch past

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 91. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf cours e, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at One Mile and Seventy Yards) (Rail at 42 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VELOCE stalked inside, tipped out to the three path and bid into the far turn, took a narrow lead passing the quarter pole and was in the five path at the top of the lane, was herded out by the inner pacesetter who tried to battle back, but held on gamely. OFFICER COUNTRY set the pace inside, was headed by an outer foe around the far turn, lost the lead passing the quarter pole and was in the four path entering the stretch, dug in and battled back while drifting out passing the eighth pole, could not get back up, but held on to place. EDEN PARADISE rated in the two path, was nudged along inside of rivals around the far turn, cued from the two path into the stretch, kept on to bid into the final furlong, but hung to show. PREFECT tracked in the three path, was roused into the far turn, floated out to the seven path into the stretch, was carried further out by an inner foe, and evened out late. SILENT CHAOS travelled inside around the first turn, settled off the pace in the three path down the backstretch, was roused between foes in the three path early around the far turn, but was stymied in the five path in upper stretch, had a seam nearing the final sixteenth, but did not factor. UNLEVERAGED bumped with an outer foe at the start, raced in midpack around the five path, fanned out to the eight path into the lane, but was empty. SUMMER SHANDEE bumped with an inner foe at the start, raced wellback in the five path but did not threaten. VALID EXCHANGE had an awkward slow start and always trailed from the three to five paths.
